            <p>Too engaging. As a parent of 2 I was way to busy for most hobbies. The quiz recommended that I “find inner peace through painting” . By the time the transformation to “zen painter” was almost complete I had become a totally distant parent. I would drink the warm sun against my skin and paint the colors. I would bathe in whalesong and sketch the songs with oil on canvas. I would sing with the brings and eternalize our songs with a soft charcoal pencil. It was very fulfilling buy totally all consuming. After several months of painting the school called and said that I was being sued for neglect. Would not recommend. <br> ~Alice from New Castle, UK </p>
